Alignment of Data

Chosen algorithm: ClustalW

Assumptions:

	•	The sequences are homologous (evolutionarily related)
	•	Independence of residues within the column and between columns of an alignment.

Limitations:

	•	Local minimum problem
	•	Choice of alignment parameters
	•	No removal of existing gaps from an already aligned sequence set. 

Script: 

% conda install -c bioconda clustalw

% cd Patho563 

% grep “>” Lamiaceae.fasta

% clustalw2 -ALIGN -INFILE=Lamiaceae.fasta -OUTFILE=Lamiaceae-aligned.fasta
